  "body": "Will truffle ever allow testing contracts in another testing framework or use a different assertion library with `truffle test`? I really like `jest`'s snapshot testing and it's BDD style assertions. When writing contract tests, I often find myself setuping up contract state, running some oprations and comparing the expected state to the actual state. This seems like the perfect job for snapshot testing.\r\n\r\nI know this can be accomplished using `truffle-contract` and writing tests without using truffle directly but then the `artifact` global along with the standard `truffle test` convention is lost.",
